---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Quickstart — llm-contract"
  description="Install llm-contract and integrate enforce(schema, run, options) in minutes."
>
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold text-white mb-4 tracking-tight"><span class="gradient-text">Quickstart</span></h1>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 text-lg max-w-3xl">
      Add a deterministic reliability boundary to any LLM call with one function:
      <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm border border-border">enforce(schema, run, options)</code>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 tracking-tight">1) Install</h2>
    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 max-w-2xl">
      <pre><code class="language-bash">npm install llm-contract zod</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 tracking-tight">2) Minimal enforce example</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 max-w-3xl mb-6">Keep your provider call. Let the contract handle clean, verify, repair, and retry.</p>
    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
      <pre><code class="language-typescript">import &#123; enforce &#125; from "llm-contract";
import &#123; z &#125; from "zod";

const schema = z.object(&#123;
  sentiment: z.enum(["positive", "negative", "neutral"]),
  confidence: z.number().min(0).max(1),
&#125;);

const result = await enforce(schema, async (attempt) =&gt; &#123;
  const response = await openai.responses.create(&#123;
    model: "gpt-4.1",
    input: [
      &#123; role: "system", content: attempt.instructions &#125;,
      &#123; role: "user", content: "Analyze: I love this product" &#125;,
      ...attempt.repairs,
    ],
  &#125;);
  return response.output_text;
&#125;);</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 tracking-tight">3) Handle the result</h2>
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4 items-start">
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
        <pre><code class="language-typescript">if (!result.ok) &#123;
  console.error(result.error.message);
  console.error(result.error.attempts);
  return;
&#125;

console.log(result.data);</code></pre>
      </div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-500 mb-3">Attempt trace</p>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-sm font-mono">
          <div class="rounded border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5 px-3 py-2"><span class="text-red-400">Attempt 1 · PARSE_ERROR</span></div>
          <div class="rounded border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/5 px-3 py-2"><span class="text-amber-400">Attempt 2 · INVARIANT_ERROR</span></div>
          <div class="rounded border border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5 px-3 py-2"><span class="text-emerald-400">Attempt 3 · SUCCESS</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 tracking-tight">Next steps</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="how-it-works" class="glass rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-accent card-hover text-sm">Understand the contract loop</a>
      <a href="api" class="glass rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-accent card-hover text-sm">Read Core API</a>
      <a href="examples" class="glass rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-accent card-hover text-sm">See full examples</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
